Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Rancho LPG Holdings LLC (Rancho) is a liquefied petroleum gas (LPG) storage facility located in San Pedro, Calif. Since 1973, the Rancho terminal has operated on North Gaffey Street directly adjacent to a local refinery.   The Rancho facility is used for seasonal storage of butane, which is a byproduct of gasoline refining. The facility also handles a small amount of propane. In the summer months, butane is temporarily stored due to California air quality requirements. In the winter months, butane is blended into gasoline. Rancho is committed to operating safely. They perform regular, planned maintenance at the facility to ensure all components remain in compliance with regulatory and company standards.  We’ve also made numerous safety upgrades in the past three years to help ensure their facility remains in good working condition.

Description: Email productivity software developer
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: KM Sciences Inc. develops email productivity software solutions.  KM Sciences has a line of fully developed software solutions that address the growing and emerging market of email productivity. The company offers EasyMailSuite, a family of products aimed at email user productivity; giving users better and richer information.  The company's flagship product, EasyLinkMail, is presented as a window displayed on the right side of the Microsoft Outlook user interface.  This window displays the most frequently accessed email information: email conversations in chronological order (including replies and forwards), participants involved, related emails, attachments and a quick reply text box which allows the user to respond to an email without starting a new message.  This format increases efficiency for users by viewing pertinent information in a side window without having to filter through or cut and paste scores of emails. The five areas that KM Sciences has addressed with their products are: conversation consolidation, productivity improvement, mailbox trimming, business networking and contact management, and survey management. KM Sciences was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Orange County, California.

Description: Landerholm Immigration is an Oakland Bay Area immigration law firm dedicated to fighting for the rights of immigrants facing deportation!
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: At Landerholm Immigration, A.P.C., we understand that immigration law is complicated, frustrating, and oftentimes even quite scary. Because our modern world has worked so hard to reduce barriers between countries, more and more families have looked to immigrate here to the United States. Nobody wants to see their family split up, so the threat of deportation or a rejected immigration application can be a devastating and terrifying proposition. That’s why we have dedicated ourselves to helping people by fighting for their right to immigrate to this country and especially here in Oakland, California, where we’re located. Whether that means serving as deportation defense lawyers, fighting to get you asylum, or battling to ensure that family immigration does not tear apart those same families it is looking to help, Landerholm Immigration, A.P.C. is ready to stand up for you. We also understand that it is important to protect those noncitizens that are already on US soil. This means protecting women through the VAWA and helping keep your children safe through DACA initiatives. We strive to make coming to and living in the United States of America a positive experience so that those we help can spread the word that our country truly cares for those it welcomes inside. Whether it is as simple as applying for a visa, or as complicated as fighting against a deportation order, our Oakland-located immigration attorneys understand that we are not just fighting court battles. We’re fighting to make the country a better, stronger, and more accepting place and the best way to do that is by opening our doors and inviting people like you inside. We aim to make a stressful experience easier by providing answers, advice, and the caring and capable advocacy you need in tackling US immigration law. Landerholm Immigration, A.P.C.
Industry Groups: Government and Military, Privacy and Security, Professional Services

Description: Designer and manufacturer of dynamic MEMS-based fiber optic components
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Lightconnect develops optical networking components based on technology invented by David Bloom, one of the company's founders, called diffractive MEMS. LIGHTCONNECT's products operate in the physical optics mode rather than the geometrics optics mode. Beam redirection results from diffraction rather than specular reflection. Consequently, motion, or displacement of the optical surface, is much smaller. Lightconnect claims that this technology enables fabrication of devices that are inherently much faster, more reliable, much smaller and much less susceptible to external environmental inputs.
Top 5 Investors: Intel Capital, U.S. Venture Partners, Morgenthaler Ventures, Sevin Rosen Funds, Incubic Venture Fund
